        "content": "<p>alexcrichton opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/7118\">PR #7118</a> from <code>alexcrichton:typed-table</code> to <code>bytecodealliance:main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>With the usage of resources and some small additions to the <code>Table</code> type we can get all the benefit of type-safety here without the boilerplates of traits, yay <code>Resource&lt;T&gt;</code> starting to pay for itself!</p>\n<p>I've done light refactorings here while I was at it:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Much of preview2-to-preview1 needed restructuring as I opted to use <code>Resource&lt;T&gt;</code> rather than the prior <code>u32</code>.</li>\n<li>Blocking functions on streams now check <code>ready()</code> and then call the non-blocking version. (avoids duplication)</li>\n<li>All <code>pollable</code> resources are now tracked automatically as children of the resource from whence they came, causing a dynamic error if the original item is destroyed before the <code>pollable</code></li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>",
